results.description: Addlestone railway station serves the town of Addlestone in the Runnymede District of Surrey, England. It is located on the Chertsey Branch of the Waterloo to Reading Line and is operated by South West Trains. The station was opened, with the branch line, on 14 February 1848 (...)
results.title: Addlestone railway station
